node.text:
We love our moms. Today is your day. Honestly, everyday should be your day. We hope you feel a fraction of the love you make us feel all year long today. You are our greatest legacy. Your hugs. Your patience. Your grace. You make imperfection look perfect most days. 
Whether you are with us, or have passed. Whether you are a step mother, mother in law, surrogate, teacher mom figure, god mom, block mom, friends  mom who became mom, sister who became mom, aunt who became mom, grandmother who became mom, mom who is also dad, young mom, teen mom, on your first kid or your fifteenth kid. 
Even if you feel most days like you are a barely surviving, or you are killing it and there is no one to see. 
To the insta mom‚Äôs trying to make it look beautifully organic. Helicopter moms. Granola moms. Anti-Vaxers. Breast feeding moms who rock out in public. Working moms. Stay at home moms. Co sleeper moms. Moms with sick kids. Moms on welfare. Pregnant moms. Foster moms. Single moms. Moms reaching for the melatonin and all the moms doing the opposite,  or something totally different. You deserve that glass of wine. We know everyone is judging you. We know you are all doing the best you can each day when it comes down to it. We know you are just trying to love your kids. We ‚ù§Ô∏è you for it. 
Thank you for letting us feed you. Especially these days... you are being asked to mom in whole new ways and you are making it work, like you always do,  because you are mom. 
Shout out to all the moms on our team  working today to take care of other  moms. 
Without moms there would be no us.

node.text: This might be a long one...and it might get emotional. Leanna and Eric aka @airside_eric aka @leannasdad and Jamie have been coming since we opened. As a restaurant owner your regulars become your family. Really. Your true family. You depend on them. You are all up in their life and they are all up in yours. You end up at their house. You go out of your way for them and they do the same. It‚Äôs beautiful. It‚Äôs poetic and you can‚Äôt manufacture it. It is, or it is not. Leanna is our love. She is The Nest baby (along with @mrsyoly_s kids and a hand full of others who I will tag below). We feel like we helped raised her. But honestly she raised us. Every smile and pancake. Today she is a young lady. Her cousin/brother The Nest is the same age as her. Every birthday we celebrate she celebrates. Eric is one of those dads that make other dads jealous and make guys that don‚Äôt have daughters want one. He is the #girldad prototype. He looooves his lady. Check out his page. His professional page as a pilot shows the other side of him and he has an insane following for his pilot work. And Jamie she is so patient. She doesn‚Äôt say much but she‚Äôs been there also providing care and consistency and her own brand of true love. This family. They have trusted us and we couldn‚Äôt love them more. If you have not found a spot to be a regular find one. Commit yourself to that small business and they will do the same for you. Find somewhere close to you who you want to invest your time talent and treasure into. We have celebrated this young woman for the last six years and we look forward to six more years if we can get thorough the Rona. Yes, we set up a party of 3 just for Leanna today but what her and Eric and Jamie give us is worth so much more. We would fly to the moon for you. Oh wait Eric already does that. Well... we will be a place to park the plane... ‚ù§Ô∏è
